You must agree to the conditions outlined in the LICENSE in order to contribute.

In order for your contribution to be noticed and accepted, you must create a pull request
that includes all modifications and explains why or how you are implementing the changes.
If your modifications create significant instability, the request will either be made
optional to the user or refused, since we are aiming for the quickest or most stable code.

This project is free and open-source, you can modify any source code and request changes
to be made to the main release stream.
